{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "targeted_sweep7_lite_inversion",
    "description": "Lite network validation of the inversion zone and committed threshold structure discovered in targeted_sweep1 on the full network.\ntargeted_sweep5 confirmed lite/full equivalence at pool_committed_split=0.35 (the baseline column), but the most complex behavior \u2014 the non-monotonic inversion zone at econ=0.60-0.70 where higher committed_split HURTS v27 \u2014 was never validated on the lite network. That inversion is the defining feature of the decision boundary and will be the primary target of Phase 3 LHS sampling. If the lite network replicates it correctly, Phase 3 can run on either network with full confidence.\nGrid design: 4 economic levels \u00d7 3 committed split values = 12 scenarios. Economic levels chosen to bracket the full boundary structure:\n  econ=0.50 \u2014 low threshold region (v27 wins at low commit, loses at higher commit)\n  econ=0.60 \u2014 inversion zone (v27 LOSES as committed_split increases)\n  econ=0.70 \u2014 inversion zone (v26 wins everywhere in sweep1)\n  econ=0.82 \u2014 above threshold (v27 wins everywhere)\n\nCommitted split values chosen to bracket the inversion behavior:\n  commit=0.20 \u2014 below Foundry flip-point (v27 wins at econ=0.50, 0.60)\n  commit=0.38 \u2014 above flip-point, mid-range (v26 wins in inversion zone)\n  commit=0.65 \u2014 high committed (v26 wins in inversion zone; v27 wins at 0.82)\n\nExpected outcomes if lite matches full (from targeted_sweep1):\n                   commit=0.20   commit=0.38   commit=0.65\n  econ=0.50           v27           v27           v27\n  econ=0.60           v27           v26           v26\n  econ=0.70           v27           v26           v26\n  econ=0.82           v27           v27           v27\n\nAny deviation from this pattern indicates a structural difference between the lite and full networks in the inversion zone dynamics \u2014 the most policy-relevant region of the parameter space.\nFixed parameters are identical to targeted_sweep1 and targeted_sweep5 throughout for direct apples-to-apples comparison.\nRuntime: ~12 scenarios \u00d7 ~30 min = ~6 hours on lite network.\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/targeted_sweep7_lite_inversion.yaml",
